This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on February 20, 2018. The memorandum delegates authorities under Section 1245 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2018 to the Secretary of State, in coordination with the Secretary of Defense, the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, and the Director of National Intelligence. The memorandum also states that these delegations will apply to any future public law provisions that are the same or substantially the same as the provision referenced in the memorandum. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.